                                                         java.lang.String level)
                                                  throws ApiException
        Returns Category Codes with their sub-categories (if exist), descriptions and SIC Codes mapping Accepts first partial digits or full category codes to filter the response
        Parameters:
        categoryCode - Specify starting digits or full category code to filter the response (optional)
        level - Allowed values are 1,2,3. If level=1, then only 4 digits category codes will be returned, level=2 means only 6 digits category codes will be returned, level=3 means only 11 digits category codes will be returned. Multiple comma-separated values will also be accepted. So level='1,2' means return 4 digits and 6 digits category codes. (optional)
        Returns:
        GeoEnrichMetadataResponse
        Throws:
        ApiException - If fail to call the API, e.g. server error or cannot deserialize the response body

      • getPOIsByAddress

        public GeoEnrichResponse getPOIsByAddress(java.lang.String address,
                                          java.lang.String country,
                                          java.lang.String name,
                                          java.lang.String type,
                                          java.lang.String categoryCode,
                                          java.lang.String sicCode,
                                          java.lang.String maxCandidates,
                                          java.lang.String searchRadius,
                                          java.lang.String searchRadiusUnit,
                                          java.lang.String travelTime,
                                          java.lang.String travelTimeUnit,
                                          java.lang.String travelDistance,
                                          java.lang.String travelDistanceUnit,
                                          java.lang.String travelMode,
                                          java.lang.String sortBy,
                                          java.lang.String fuzzyOnName,
                                          java.lang.String page,
                                          java.lang.String matchMode,
                                          java.lang.String specificMatchOn)
                                   throws ApiException
        Points of Interest By Address. Accepts address as an input to retrieve nearby points of interest.
        Parameters:
        address - Address (required)
        country - Country (optional)
        name - Matched against Name, BrandName and Trade Name. Partial terms are also matched with fuzziness (max edit distance is 1) (optional)
        type - Matched against the content which defines the type of the poi. (optional)
        categoryCode - Specific Category/Categories Codes for the desired POIs. Accepts a mix of 4 digit (Top Category), 6 digit (Second-Level Category) and 11 digit (Low-Level Category) Category Codes. https://developer.precisely.com/download?CategoryCodes.xlsx (optional)
        sicCode - Specific SIC Codes/Codes for the desired POIs. Accepts a mix of 4 digit (Top Category) and 8 digit (Low-Level Category) SIC Codes. (optional)
        maxCandidates - Maximum number of POIs that can be retrieved. (optional)
        searchRadius - Radius range within which search is performed. (optional)
        searchRadiusUnit - Radius unit such as Feet, Kilometers, Miles or Meters. (optional)
        travelTime - Specifies the travel time within which method searches for results (POIs which can be reached within travel time)the search boundary in terms of time mentioned in 'travelTimeUnit'. The results are retrieved from the polygon formed based on the travel time specified. This means search can be done in the mentioned time results be from the mentioned time. (optional)
        travelTimeUnit - Specifies acceptable time units.Allowed values Minutes,Hours,Seconds and Milliseconds (optional)
        travelDistance - Specifies the search boundary in terms of distance mentioned in 'travelDistanceUnit'. The results are retrieved from the polygon formed based on the travel distance specified. (optional)
        travelDistanceUnit - Specifies acceptable time units.Allowed values Feet,Kilometers,Miles and Meters (optional)
        travelMode - Specifies the available mode of commute. This is required when u r trying to do search by travel distance or travel time. Allowed values driving and walking (optional)
        sortBy - Specifies the order in which POIs are retrieved. (optional, default to distance)
        fuzzyOnName - Allowed values are Y/N. If N, the search on name will not allow fuzziness. (optional)
        page - Will support pagination, by default 1st page with maxCandidates results are returned. (optional)
        matchMode - (optional)
        specificMatchOn - (optional)
        Returns:
        GeoEnrichResponse
        Throws:
        ApiException - If fail to call the API, e.g. server error or cannot deserialize the response body

        Points of Interest Autocomplete. POIs-Autocomplete will return POIs predictions based on the full or partial words specified in the search.The search can then be narrowed based on Location, IP Address or Country along with other supporting filters.
        Parameters:
        longitude - Longitude of the location. (optional)
        latitude - Latitude of the location. (optional)
        searchText - Matched against Name, BrandName and Trade Name. Partial terms are also matched with fuzziness (max edit distance is 1) (optional)
        searchRadius - Radius range within which search is performed. (optional)
        searchRadiusUnit - Radius unit such as Feet, Kilometers, Miles or Meters. (optional)
        travelTime - Specifies the travel time within which method searches for results (POIs which can be reached within travel time)the search boundary in terms of time mentioned in 'travelTimeUnit'. The results are retrieved from the polygon formed based on the travel time specified. This means search can be done in the mentioned time results be from the mentioned time. (optional)
        travelTimeUnit - Specifies acceptable time units.Allowed values Minutes,Hours,Seconds and Milliseconds (optional)
        travelDistance - Specifies the search boundary in terms of distance mentioned in 'travelDistanceUnit'. The results are retrieved from the polygon formed based on the travel distance specified. (optional)
        travelDistanceUnit - Specifies acceptable time units.Allowed values Feet,Kilometers,Miles and Meters (optional)
        travelMode - Specifies the available mode of commute. This is required when u r trying to do search by travel distance or travel time. Allowed values driving and walking (optional)
        country - Country (optional)
        areaName1 - Specifies the largest geographical area, typically a state or province. (optional)
        areaName3 - Specifies the name of the city or town. (optional)
        postcode1 - Postal Code of the input to be searched (optional)
        postcode2 - Postcode2 (optional)
        ipAddress - IP address of network connected device in standard IPv4 octet and a valid external address. (optional)
        autoDetectLocation - Specifies whether to auto-detect location from IP address. If 'True' is set, the location is detected from the specified ip address. If 'False' is set. the search will happen according to country or location. (optional)
        type - Matched against the content which defines the type of the poi. (optional)
        categoryCode - Specific Category/Categories Codes for the desired POIs. Accepts a mix of 4 digit (Top Category), 6 digit (Second-Level Category) and 11 digit (Low-Level Category) Category Codes. https://developer.precisely.com/download?CategoryCodes.xlsx (optional)
        sicCode - Specific SIC Codes/Codes for the desired POIs. Accepts a mix of 4 digit (Top Category) and 8 digit (Low-Level Category) SIC Codes. (optional)
        maxCandidates - Maximum number of POIs that can be retrieved. (optional)
        sortBy - Specifies the order in which POIs are retrieved. (optional, default to distance)
        searchOnNameOnly - specifies search on name (optional)
        matchMode - (optional)
        specificMatchOn - (optional)
        Returns:
        ApiResponse<GeoEnrichResponse>
        Throws:
        ApiException - If fail to call the API, e.g. server error or cannot deserialize the response body
